her, saying: "You're not going to take Debbie away from me." Clayton was 
arrested at a hospital, where she received six stitches for cuts to her 
fingers. 
</P>
<P>
Clayton had worked as a jet mechanic and had been in the Navy for eight years, 
according to the probation report. 
</P>
<P>
The "other woman" listed in the report said her relationship with Clayton ended 
a month and a half before the slaying because of her interest in Dupee. 
