HART GIRLS OPEN STATE TOURNAMENT AT HOME TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The state high school basketball tournament begins tonight with the opening 
round in 10 boys' and girls' divisions. 
</P>
<P>
In the girls' Division I field of the Southern California region, third-seeded 
Hart (25-2), the Southern Section 5-A Division champion, plays host to 5-AA 
runner-up Fontana (27-2) at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
Crenshaw, the City Section 4-A champion, is top-seeded in the boys' Division I 
field. The Cougars (21-2) will play San Diego Section champion Poway at Cal 
State Dominguez Hills at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
Defending state champion Manual Arts (24-1), which lost to Crenshaw, 85-72, in 
the City championship game last Friday, received an at-large bid and will play 
Capistrano Valley (24-4) at Saddleback College. 
</P>
<P>
Fremont (25-3), the City 3-A champion, will travel to Long Beach to play 
Millikan (25-6), the Southern Section 5-AA Division champion. 
</P>
<P>
The regional semifinals will be held Thursday with the finals Saturday at the 
Sports Arena and Cal State Dominguez Hills. LONNIE WHITE 
