<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY EARNINGS: MARTIN LAWRENCE GALLERIES REPORTS $1.6-MILLION PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Martin Lawrence Limited Editions said its profit climbed 75% to $1.6 million in 
the fourth quarter, ending Dec. 31, from a year earlier. Sales rose 37% to $9.2 
million. 
</P>
<P>
The Van Nuys chain of art galleries, which is expanding rapidly by opening 
galleries in shopping malls and other locations, earned $5.8 million last year, 
up 92% from 1987. Sales in 1988 rose 50% from a year earlier, to $34.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
For detailed data and results of other companies, please see tables, Page 10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
