<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At Warner Bros., Brian De Palma is slated to direct Tom Wolfe's piercing 
portrayal of New York society, "The Bonfire of the Vanities." Michael Cristofer 
will adapt Wolfe's best-selling novel for the big screen. No cast has been set. 
De Palma will begin production on the film this summer after he wraps up 
"Casualties of War" for Columbia. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
