The cornerstone of the $11-million land sale by the Santa Monica Mountains 
Conservancy was the site of the ceremony, the 1,655-acre Circle X Ranch in 
southeast Ventura County, which includes Sandstone Peak, the highest point in 
the Santa Monicas. The ranch and 779 acres in Malibu's Zuma Canyon were added 
to the Santa Monica Mountains National Recreation Area. 
