<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lotus Wins Court Case: Lotus Development Corp. announced that a federal judge 
has dismissed all claims made by SAPC Inc. against Lotus and its founder, 
Mitchell D. Kapor. In November, U.S. District Judge Robert E. Keeton dismissed 
SAPC's claim of copyright infringement, ruling that SAPC gave up its right to 
sue when it sold most of its assets to Lotus in 1985. Keeton dismissed all 
remaining charges against Lotus and Kapor last week. Those claims included 
charges of breach of contract, misappropriation of trade secrets and 
confidential secrets and unjust enrichment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
LOTUS DEVELOPMENT CORP; COPYRIGHT; SAPC INC; BREACH OF CONTRACT; TRADE SECRETS; 
INDUSTRIAL ESPIONAGE 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA030789-0101 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 27663 </DOCID>
<DATE>
