<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newsweek Scoops Time: Newsweek magazine scooped its chief rival, Time, on one 
of the biggest business deals of the year: the $18-billion proposed merger 
between Time Inc. and Warner Communications Inc. Newsweek included a two-page 
story on the proposed deal in its March 13 issue, but this week's Time is 
silent on the merger that was announced hours before the magazines went to 
press Saturday night. "We never intended to cover the merger in the news 
pages," Time spokesman Louis J. Slovinsky said. 
</P>
