<P>
DRIVERS SHOULD EXPECT COAST HIGHWAY DELAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Motorists should expect some disruption and inconvenience on Pacific Coast 
Highway between 9th and Main streets through March 17 as city construction 
crews finish drainage improvements in the area. 
</P>
<P>
Work on the Pacific Coast Highway Flood Control Improvement Project may mean 
that traffic will be periodically reduced to a single lane in each directions 
on the highway, said William G. Reed, city public information officer. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, parking may be temporarily banned on the highway in places where 
it would normally be allowed, and turns onto or off the road may be restricted 
at certain corners. 
</P>
