<P>
OCTD APPROVES PLAN FOR MONORAIL TO AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A developer's plan to build a privately financed monorail between John Wayne 
Airport and an Irvine office center received unanimous support Monday from 
Orange County Transit District board members. 
</P>
<P>
Transit agency board members praised McDonnell Douglas Realty Co., the firm 
that has offered to pay for the $3.5-million, half-mile monorail. It would link 
the company's 23-story twin office towers in Douglas Plaza with the new 
passenger terminal, which is due to open in April, 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Board members said private financing for such facilities is welcome and 
necessary because government does not have the money to build them. 
</P>
<P>
Construction is expected to begin later this year. 
</P>
<P>
The vote came at the board's meeting Monday at OCTD headquarters in Garden 
Grove. 
