<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A social worker pulled out of the race against Councilman Ernani Bernardi today 
and endorsed the councilman's leading challenger, firefighter and community 
activist Lyle Hall. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Yanez, 28, a county psychiatric social worker who lives in Sylmar, said 
he dropped his challenge to Bernardi because it became obvious "that Lyle Hall 
is going to be the next councilman of the 7th District." 
</P>
<P>
Yanez said he endorsed Hall because he was more responsive to community needs. 
Bernardi has neglected some neighborhoods and has not helped residents campaign 
against development, Yanez told a City Hall news conference. Bernardi was 
attending a City Council meeting and was not immediately available for comment. 
</P>
<P>
Yanez said he believed that Hall can beat Bernardi. 
</P>
<P>
"I thought I had a chance, but I think his chance is better," Yanez said of 
Hall. 
