<P>
ARREST SIDELINES UNR'S OWENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RENO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Darryl Owens of Nevada-Reno, the Big Sky Conference's leading scorer, 
apparently will miss the conference basketball tournament that starts Thursday 
after being suspended following his arrest on a misdemeanor battery charge. 
</P>
<P>
Owens is free on $265 bail after being arrested Monday on the complaint filed 
by a woman identified as his former girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
UNR coach Len Stevens announced the indefinite suspension at a news conference, 
praising Owens' leadership but saying he could not be an exception because of 
his basketball talents. 
</P>
<P>
The incident involving the woman allegedly occurred in the Stead area north of 
Reno and while few details are available, university spokesman Bob Gabrielli 
said the woman was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
Owens is averaging 22.7 points a game this year to lead the Big Sky by a 
fraction over the 22.5-point average of Weber State's Rico Washington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
